Make your button a default button:

     button.setDefaultButton(true);

From the [javadoc](https://openjfx.io/javadoc/17/javafx.controls/javafx/scene/control/Button.html#setDefaultButton(boolean)):

&gt; A default Button is the button that receives a keyboard VK_ENTER press, if no other node in the scene consumes it.

Alternately see:

 * https://stackoverflow.com/questions/69059227/how-to-set-an-action-to-occur-on-pressing-of-any-keyboard-key-in-javafx
 * https://stackoverflow.com/questions/13880638/how-do-i-pick-up-the-enter-key-being-pressed-in-javafx2

Which provides this solution:

    scene.setOnKeyPressed( event -&gt; {
      if( event.getCode() == KeyCode.ENTER ) {
        doSomething();
      }
    } );

If you want to intercept enter when something else has focus you can use an event filter instead of the set on key pressed.

