As per [Java 14 JLS, &#167;9.5][JLS]:
&gt; Every member type declaration in the body of an interface is implicitly `public` and `static`.

Thus, one cannot access `this` in a field initializer.

The common way to work around this limitation is to provide a method that returns what is needed. Possibly, as [default method][OracleDefaultMethods] (requires Java 8+): 

    public interface Foo {
        public default String fooName() {
            return this.getClass().getName();
        }
    }

