Anytime a method member of a generic class _`C&lt;T&gt;`_, *takes in* (i.e. *consumes*) an argument that is of type _`T`_, then that method is a *consumer of `T`s*.

So [_`Comparator&lt;T&gt;.compareTo(T o)`_](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/14/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/Comparable.html#compareTo(T)) is said to be a *consumer* of the _`o`_ object of the type represented by the type variable _`T`_.

